@node author "Author"


Just some dull stuff:

I'm a 21 year old student living in Finland. I'm also
a soccer/SWOS/Amiga/C64 enthusiast, as you can see. Anyway I haven't been
quite productive in past years, this has been the only big project so far.

My computer setup

Amiga 1200T (Infinitiv tower)
Blizzard 1230-IV 50 MHz
18 Mb Ram
3,2 Gb HD
4xCD Rom
14" Multisync Monitor

If you find bugs on this guide or have any opinions about this project or so,
don't hesitate to contact me!

E-Mail

pasiyx2@hotmail.com

Snail Mail

Pasi Ylinen
Mutkatie 9
74200 Vieremä
Finland

(I'm not responding via Snail-mail if you don't put enough stamps
there to cover the costs of responding...)

IRC

Peto
(I'm usually on channels #amiga #amigafin #c-64 #c64 (IRCNET)
or #britishsoccerchat (CHATNET))


@endnode
@node thanks "Thanks"


Thanks go to...


- Peter Fischer  (fixing German letters, some gameresults,
finding that bug etc. You have really been big help so far!)

- A.Nieuwenhuizen   (correcting some Dutch data)

- Marcus Stratmann  (correcting a few German playernames)

I would also like to thank everyone, who has bothered to mail me
comments etc.




@endnode
@node registration "Registration"


This guide is actually freeware, so you don't have to pay me anything
if you don't want to. But of course paying is not prohibited!

@endnode
@node history "History"

This project has really lasted a long time.. From time to time I lost
my interests towards this guide as it took so lots of time to do.
I might have made this guide in a better way, but I wanted to put
this guide fast (hah!) together.
I started this project because I wasn't able to get my hands on any
soccer-related CD-Roms available for Amiga. Now there seems to be
History Of The World Cup but I haven't bought it yet....

Version           Description                                  Date

0.1               Guide containing 1930-1938                   12.6.1996
0.2               Added 1950-1954                              13.6.1996
0.3               Added 1958                                    7.9.1996
0.4               Added 1962-1970                              10.1.1997
0.5               Added 1974-1978                              13.3.1997
0.6               Added 1982                                   20.3.1997
0.7               Added 1986                                   21.3.1997
0.8               Added 1990                                    2.4.1997
0.9               Added 1994                                    9.4.1997
1.0               Checked information etc.                     28.9.1997
                  -FIRST AMINET RELEASE-
1.01              Fixed the first and hopefully last bug :)   26.11.1997
                  (thanks to Peter Fischer for finding it)
                  Some spelling corrections.
1.02              Putting more information into France 1998    7.12.1997
1.03              Added 4 missing game datas.                  11.1.1998
                  Some little fixes on playerdata.
                  Guide contains now fixed German letters.
1.04              Again corrected some wrongly spelled names   24.1.1998
                  Some little fixes, which you wont probably
                  recognize at all :)
@endnode
@node future "future"

Well, there's not a lot things planned, just overall fixing.
(at least nothing major will be done before World Cup in France)...


But anyway,

- There's still a few missing game results, maybe some misspelled names etc.
- That Brazilian Ademir is a big questionmark, other sources show that
  he's scored 9 goals in 1950, but others show that he has only made 7 goals.
  I believe myself that he's scored 7 goals, as I can't find any games, where
  he would have scored those "missing" 2 goals.

I really hope that if you find some statistics/names etc.
are wrong and you know the correct ones please report about it to me.

@endnode
